<h4>Weekly Deaths vs Case Fatality Rate (CFR)</h4>

<p>
Most reporting on COVID-19 danger is for the risk of dying
<b>if you get covid-19</b>.
But what is your risk of getting COVID-19?
Your risk of dying <b>if you have</b> active
<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tuberculosis">tuberculosis</a> is
<a href="https://www.who.int/news-room/fact-sheets/detail/tuberculosis">
almost 50%</a>!
Yet those of us fortunate enough to live in the developed world, do not
consider tuberculosis a danger.
</p>

<p>
<em>Weekly deaths per million people</em> is a rough measurement of the
<em>combined</em> risk of getting covid-19 and then dying from it.
</p>

